        processedAt

This keeps source data immutable.

12. Priority Scoring

The AI should never output only "High" or "Low".

Use a score:

0-100

Built from multiple factors.

Example framework:

Priority Score

=

Issue Severity      (30%)

Citizen Frequency   (25%)

Infrastructure Risk (20%)

Location Importance (15%)

Confidence          (10%)

Even if the first version uses heuristic values, the interface remains stable.

13. Recommendation Engine

Instead of merely classifying issues, generate actionable recommendations.

Example:

{
  "recommendation": {
    "action": "Repair street lighting on MG Road",
    "reason": "High citizen frequency and safety impact",
    "priority": "Immediate"
  }
}
